(1) The Registrar shall keep and maintain a Roll of Notaries Public in which shall be entered— (a) the name, address and signature of every person who is appointed a notary public under this Act; (b) the name and address of every person deemed to have been appointed as a notary public under this Act, pursuant to section twenty-nine; (c) in respect of every entry made under paragraph (b), a reference, by volume number and page, to the signed entry in the Roll of Legal Practitioners in respect of the admission of such person as a notary public under any earlier law; (d) such other particulars as are prescribed pursuant to subsection (2).
