(2) The Chief Justice may by rule made by statutory instrument, from time to time, prescribe the form of the said Roll and any particulars in respect of each notary public, in addition to his name and address, which shall be entered therein, and may, from time to time, in like manner, alter, amend or revoke any rule made pursuant to this subsection.
